%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%20workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20quit%20when%20companies%20have%20strict%20return-to-office%20mandates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Commuters%20arrive%20on%20Wall%20Street%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bac77743bb77284ba252e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStrict%20return-to-office%20mandates%20can%20make%20top%20workers%20want%20to%20leave.%3Cp%3EMark%20Lennihan%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETop%20workers%20are%2016%25%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20a%20job%20when%20an%20employer%20is%20strict%20on%20office%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-workers-getting-boot-again-rto-wayfair-tech-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20also%20put%20off%20workers%20in%20general%2C%20according%20to%20Gartner.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20research%20firm%20said%20women%2C%20millennials%20are%20likelier%20to%20want%20to%20leave%20jobs%20with%20strict%20RTO%20rules.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20a%20star%20at%20work%20but%20your%20boss%20makes%20you%20head%20into%20the%20office%2C%20you're%20more%20likely%20to%20start%20hunting%20for%20a%20new%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gartner.com%2Fen%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2F2024-01-30-gartner-hr-research-finds-high-performers-women-millennials-are-greatest-flight-risks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGartner%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20high-performing%20workers%20are%2016%25%20less%20inclined%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20jobs%20when%20employers%20roll%20out%20strict%20return-to-office%20mandates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner%20defined%20the%20high-performers%20as%20those%20advancing%20more%20quickly%20in%20their%20career%20than%20their%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20from%20a%20survey%20of%20nearly%202%2C100%20white-collar%20workers%20come%20as%20major%20employers%2C%20from%20banks%20to%20tech%20companies%2C%20push%20their%20people%20to%20head%20to%20the%20office.%20UPS%20on%20Tuesday%20announced%20big%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fups-layoffs-ceo-soft-demand-high-labor-costs-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecuts%20to%20its%20executive%20ranks%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20said%20it%20would%20require%20those%20remaining%20to%20be%20in%20five%20days%20a%20week.%20Other%20major%20companies%20have%20said%20employees%20who%20skip%20their%20commutes%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-return-to-office-mandate-be-fired-amazon-meta-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epay%20a%20price%20in%20their%20reviews%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cubicle%20callback%20also%20comes%20amid%20mixed%20signals%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-remote-jobs-more-productive-work-life-balance-return-office-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehow%20important%20it%20is%20to%20always%20be%20in%20the%20office%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20recent%20study%20suggested%20companies%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-remote-work-stock-returns-productivity-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erequire%20time%20in%20the%20office%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20actually%20aren't%20more%20profitable%20or%20productive.%20But%20the%20effect%20of%20rigid%20RTO%20requests%20isn't%20necessarily%20limited%20to%20what%20shows%20up%20on%20a%20balance%20sheet%2C%20Caitlin%20Duffy%2C%20a%20research%20director%20in%20the%20Gartner%20HR%20practice%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReturn-to-office%20mandates%20are%20a%20very%20risky%20proposition.%20They%20may%20be%20more%20about%20what%20leaders%20want%20than%20what%20really%20benefits%20employees%2C%20both%20personally%20and%20professionally%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGartner's%20survey%2C%20conducted%20from%20May%20through%20June%202023%2C%20showed%20that%20employees%2C%20in%20general%2C%20were%208%25%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stick%20around%20when%20bosses%20put%20in%20an%20inflexible%20RTO%20mandate.%20Among%20women%2C%2011%25%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay.%20That's%20partly%20because%20women%20often%20value%20flexibility%20and%20might%20feel%20they%20face%20less%20bias%20when%20they're%20not%20in%20the%20office%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20among%20millennials%2C%20who%20Gartner%20said%20were%20most%20likely%20to%20have%20to%20juggle%20caregiving%20duties%2C%20tight%20rules%20about%20being%20in%20the%20office%20made%20them%2010%25%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20stay%20at%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20wanting%20to%20quit%20and%20leaving%20are%20two%20different%20things.%20Still%2C%20Duffy%20said%2C%20having%20unhappy%20workers%20stick%20around%20can%20be%20its%20own%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20the%20best%20out%20of%20those%20employees%20if%20they're%20people%20who%20are%20looking%20to%20leave%20at%20the%20next%20possible%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuffy%20said%20there's%20a%20benefit%20to%20bringing%20workers%20together.%20The%20survey%20showed%20employee%20engagement%20rose%20for%20most%20workers%2C%20particularly%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20when%20they%20were%20required%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office.%C2%A0But%2C%20she%20said%2C%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20buy%20into%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20office%20when%20they%20understand%20why%20going%20in%20would%20be%20helpful%20and%20when%20they've%20had%20a%20hand%20in%20crafting%20the%20office%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20successful%20than%20an%20arbitrary%20requirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20attendance%20at%20the%20office%20can%20also%20rankle%20high-performing%20employees%2C%20she%20said%2C%20because%20they're%20often%20stretched%20and%20need%20autonomy%20to%20work%20in%20a%20way%20that's%20best%20for%20them.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20their%20performance%2C%20they%20should%20be%20trusted%20to%20structure%20their%20workdays%20and%20have%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20leaders%20often%20get%20wrong%20is%20thinking%20that%20employees%20are%20just%20trying%20to%20do%20less%20work%20or%20get%20more%20out%20of%20their%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Duffy%20said.%20%26quot%3BEmployees%20want%20to%20perform%20well%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20be%20trusted%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they%20know%20their%20work%20best.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrict-return-to-office-mandates-could-drive-away-top-workers-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706781601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bac7c7ac2de4f17ee6768e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrict-return-to-office-mandates-could-drive-away-top-workers-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Employers%20that%20don't%20give%20workers%20leeway%20about%20when%20they%20head%20to%20the%20office%20could%20risk%20driving%20away%20top%20performers%2C%20a%20Gartner%20survey%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrict-return-to-office-mandates-could-drive-away-top-workers-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20is%20stepping%20up%20to%20save%20its%20economy%20this%20