mpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20Don't%20Live%20There%26quot%3B%3A%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar's%20Daughter%20On%20%26quot%3BMove%20Out%26quot%3B%20Notice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESenior%20Congress%20leader%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar's%20daughter%20Suranya%20Aiyar%2C%20who%20was%20asked%20to%20vacate%20%26quot%3Btheir%26quot%3B%20house%20in%20south-east%20Delhi%20over%20her%20Ram%20Temple%20post%2C%20has%20said%20that%20she%20doesn't%20even%20live%20there.%20%26quot%3BThe%20relevant%20Residents'%20Welfare%20Association%20is%20from%20a%20colony%20where%20I%20do%20not%20live!%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20a%20Facebook%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20residents'%20welfare%20association%20in%20Jangpura%2C%20in%20a%20letter%2C%20asked%20Mr%20Aiyar%20and%20her%20daughter%20to%20leave%20the%20colony.%20In%20the%20letter%2C%20the%20RWA%20president%20said%20the%20association%20was%20approached%20by%20residents%20of%20the%20colony%20over%20her%20social%20media%20%26quot%3Bstand%2Frant%26quot%3B%20against%20the%20consecration%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RWA%20accused%20Suranya%20of%20%26quot%3Bhate%20speech%26quot%3B%20and%20requested%20her%20to%20follow%20the%20norms%20of%20a%20good%20citizen.%20It%20claimed%20the%20colony%20was%20inhabited%20by%20residents%20who%20came%20to%20India%20from%20Pakistan%20after%20partition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20erupted%20when%20the%2049-year-old%2C%20in%20a%20Facebook%20post%20on%20January%2020%2C%20had%20claimed%20that%20she%20was%20fasting%20in%20protest%20against%20the%20'pran%20pratishtha'%20ceremony%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir.%20She%20said%20it%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20love%20and%20sorrow%20for%20fellow%20Muslim%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20Ms%20Aiyar%20said%20through%20social%20media%20was%20unbecoming%20of%20an%20educated%20person%2C%20who%20should%20have%20understood%20that%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20was%20being%20built%20after%20500%20year