cial%20budget%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20and%20Beaver%20wrote%20in%20the%20military%20news%20site%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realcleardefense.com%2Farticles%2F2024%2F01%2F29%2Fthe_defense_departments_china_military_power_report_the_threat_is_worse_than_advertised_1008012.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERealClearDefense.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20and%20Beaver%20wrote%20that%20the%20Pentagon's%20assessment%20failed%20to%20account%20for%20China's%20military%20research%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20sum%20would%20be%20significant%2C%20they%20wrote%2C%20given%20the%20amount%20that%20the%20US%20spends%20for%20this%20purpose.%20The%20Defense%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FReleases%2FRelease%2FArticle%2F3326875%2Fdepartment-of-defense-releases-the-presidents-fiscal-year-2024-defense-budget%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520FY%25202024%2520budget%2520request%2Ccredible%2520forces%2520across%2520all%2520domains.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequested%20%24145%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20research%2C%20development%2C%20and%20testing%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20also%20operates%20a%20%26quot%3Bcivil-military%20fusion%26quot%3B%20strategy%2C%20which%20allows%20its%20military%20to%20access%20intellectual%20property%20and%20technology%20from%20its%20civilian%20sectors%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConfusingly%2C%20the%20report%20does%20not%20attempt%20to%20account%20for%20either%20of%20these%20significant%20considerations%20in%20its%20treatment%20of%20China's%20defense%20budget%20topline%2C%26quot%3B%20Peters%20and%20Beaver%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChina%20can%20pay%20its%20soldiers%20a%20lot%20less%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20China's%20higher%20spending%20power%20means%20a%20smaller%20budget%20can%20go%20a%20lot%20further%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20Beijing%20pays%20its%20soldiers%20a%20lot%20less%20than%20the%20US%20does%2C%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%20Chinese%20recruits%20earn%20a%20reported%20%24108%20per%20month%2C%20per%20an%20oft-cited%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fgraphic-detail%2F2021%2F05%2F01%2Fnominal-spending-figures-understate-chinas-military-might%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Economist%20in%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%2016%20times%20lower%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-military-service-members-make-2019-2%23e-1-20340-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%2C900%20salary%20for%20US%20recruits.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeters%20and%20Beaver%20estimated%20that%20in%20general%2C%20%26quot%3BChinese%20military%20personnel%20earn%20only%20about%20one-fourth%20what%20American%20servicemembers%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSimply%20put%2C%20defense%20spending%20goes%20a%20lot%20further%20in%20China%20than%20it%20does%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20because%20labor%20and%20material%20costs%20are%20lower%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20true%20military%20spending%20has%20drawn%20renewed%20attention%20after%20Sen.%20Dan%20Sullivan%20of%20Alaska%20said%20in%20September%20that%20internal%20US%20assessments%20indicate%20Beijing's%20annual%20defense%20budget%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F09%2F19%2Fchina-defense-budget-military-weapons-purchasing-power%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24700%20billion%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecompared%20to%20Beijing's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fenglish.scio.gov.cn%2Fchinavoices%2F2023-03%2F06%2Fcontent_85146919.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20%24224%20billion%20for%202023.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Stavridis%2C%20former%20supreme%20allied%20commander%20for%20the%20National%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organization%2C%20said%20in%20September%20that%20if%20China's%20budget%20was%20truly%20%24700%20billion%2C%20it%20is%20growing%20quickly%20and%20would%20account