has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20my%20third%20year%20at%20Nanyang%20Technological%20University%20in%20Singapore%20when%20I%20cofounded%20a%20media%20company%20with%20three%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20really%20a%20conscious%20decision%20to%20start%20a%20company.%20Instead%2C%20it%20started%20off%20as%20a%20school%20project%20for%20one%20of%20our%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20videos%20we%20worked%20on%20for%20our%20class%20went%20viral%2C%20which%20is%20when%20we%20started%20thinking%20about%20creating%20our%20own%20platform.%20All%20four%20of%20us%20had%20a%20passion%20for%20telling%20local%20stories%2C%20but%20at%20the%20time%2C%20there%20weren't%20many%20career%20opportunities%20in%20this%20space%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20wanted%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20what%20we%20love%20and%20be%20able%20to%20earn%20from%20it.%20So%20we%20decided%20to%20turn%20the%20project%20into%20a%20company%20named%20%26quot%3BOur%20Grandfather%20Story%26quot%3B%20and%20began%20pursuing%20it%20full-time%20after%20graduating%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20seven%20years%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20video%20producing%2C%20editing%2C%20and%20leading%20the%20content%20team.%20In%20my%20final%20years%20with%20the%20company%2C%20I%20headed%20the%20product%20growth%20and%20development%20team%20and%20worked%20on%20developing%20our%20YouTube%20page.%20Our%20team%20grew%20to%2050%20employees%20and%20our%20best-performing%20video%2C%20about%20a%20Singapore%20restaurant%20which%20serves%20pay-as-you-wish%20meals%2C%20has%20surpassed%209.7%20million%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThinking%20about%20my%20personal%20journey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20time%20I%20was%20also%20thinking%20of%20my%20personal%20journey.%20I%20was%20a%20student%20when%20we%20first%20started%20and%20had%20not%20made%20myself%20a%20ten-year%20plan%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20around%20five%20years%20on%20the%20job%2C%20I%20started%20thinking%20about%20what's%20next.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20more%20intentional%20with%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20first%20started%20seeding%20in%20my%20mind%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20during%20The%20Great%20Resignation.%20They%20say%20that%20resignations%20are%20contagious%2C%20but%20I%20told%20myself%20to%20hold%20on%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wanted%20the%20decision%20to%20come%20from%20within%20and%20not%20because%20I%20was%20being%20influenced%20by%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother's%20passing%20from%20cancer%20in%202022%20also%20affected%20me%20deeply.%20She%20loved%20her%20work%20as%20a%20human%20resources%20professional.%20She%20worked%20throughout%20her%20sickness%2C%20even%20when%20she%20had%20an%20IV%20drip%20attached%20to%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20of%20her%20generation%20work%20towards%20retirement%20and%20only%20then%20start%20thinking%20about%20their%20bucket%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20her%20passing%20just%20at%20the%20cusp%20of%20retirement%20was%20not%20what%20motivated%20me%20to%20make%20the%20call.%20It%20was%20more%20the%20observation%20that%20her%20last%2010%20years%20of%20work%20were%20a%20lot%20more%20meaningful%20to%20her.%20In%20those%20years%2C%20she%20switched%20between%20work%20and%20rest.%20That's%20the%20kind%20of%20relationship%20I%20realized%20I%20wanted%20with%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221195%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Girl%20in%20hiking%20gear%20and%20sunglasses%20smiling%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b9f5d3ac2de4f17ee612f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22957%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECheah%20wanted%20to%20be%20more%20intentional%20with%20her%20career%20and%20was%20inspired%20by%20her%20mother's%20relationship%20with%20work.%3Cp%3ECheah%20Wenqi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBurnout%20also%20played%20a%20role%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20own%20a%20business%2C%20the%20work%20almost%20never%20ends.%20Being%20a%20founder%2C%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20flexibility%20and%20I%20could%20take%20breaks%20when%20I%20really%20needed%20one.%20But%20my%20mind%20was%20always%20working%2C%20even%20on%20vacation%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20weekends%2C%20I%20would%20worry%20about%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20week%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20personality%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20media%20industry%20also%20played%20a%20role%20in%20my%20burnout.%20TikTok%20never%20sleeps%2C%20Instagram%20never%20sleeps%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fact%2C%20it%20comes%20alive%20when%20everybody%20else%20gets%20off%20work.%20I%20was%20constantly%20looking%20out%20for%20the%20next%20idea%2C%20the%20next%20story%2C%20and%20the%20next%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20made%20me%20finally%20decide%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20comfortable%20leaving%20my%20job%20because%20I%20am%20debt%20free%2C%20have%20no%20loans%2C%20and%20no%20family%20that%20relies%20on%20me.%20I'm%20lucky%20to%20have%20reached%20the%20perfect%20timing%20where%20I%20don't%20have%20kids%20of%20my%20own%20yet%2C%20and%20my%20father%20and%20others%20in%20the%20family%20are%20still%20healthy.%20I%20live%20in%20my%20parents'%20home%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20pay%20rent%20and%20don't%20have%20a%20housing%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents'%20supportive%20reactions%20also%20struck%20me.%20My%20dad%20said%20he%20would%20do%20the%20same%20if%20he%20was%20in%20my%20place.%20I%20had%20also%20discussed%20the%20idea%20with%20my%20mum%20before%20she%20passed%20and%20she%20didn't%20even%20ask%20me%20why.%20She%20just%20asked%20me%20where%20I%20would%20travel%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quit%20my%20job%20in%20December%202023%2C%20seven%20years%20after%20founding%20Our%20Grandfather%20Story.%20I'm%20still%20a%20member%20of%20the%20board%20and%20own%20my%20share%20of%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20currently%20in%20Singapore%2C%20but%20I%20bought%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20to%20Japan%20and%20I%20fly%20out%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20no%20plans%20to%20return%20to%20the%20company%20or%20get%20another%20job%20any%20time%20soon.%20The%20next%20year%20and%20a%20half%20is%20about%20traveling%20to%20Japan%2C%20China%2C%20and%20Central%20Asia%20and%20really%20taking%20it%20one%20day%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-break-founder-burnout-quit-company-travel-singapore-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706760388000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b9f8e043bb77284ba1f517%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-break-founder-burnout-quit-company-travel-singapore-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cheah%20Wenqi%20cofounded%20a%20media%20company%20in%20Singapore%20with%20three%20university%20classmates.%20Five%20years%20later%2C%20she%20started%20thinking%20about%20what's%20next.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sgoel%40insider.com%20(Shubhangi%20Goel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-break-founder-burnout-quit-company-travel-singapore-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tracy%20Chapman%20to%20Perform%20%E2%80%98Fast%20Car%E2%80%99%20With%20Luke%20Combs%20at%20Grammys%2C%20Sources%20Say%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706759877000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FMixCollage-30-Jan-2024-12-58-PM-5314.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235891995%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tracy%20Chapman%2C%20who%20has%20not%20performed%20in%20public%20in%20years