0anti-conservative%20bias%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERarely%20does%20Congress%20land%20any%20real%20blows.%20Often%2C%20it's%20a%20complete%20whiff%2C%20and%20lawmakers%20embarrass%20themselves%20with%20their%20lack%20of%20understanding%20of%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20like%20someone%20asking%20Sundar%20Pichai%20why%20an%20unflattering%20article%20about%20the%20senator%20appeared%20on%20his%20iPhone%2C%20to%20which%20the%20Google%20CEO%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ceo-sundar-pichai-testimony-congress-waste-of-time-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECongressman%2C%20the%20iPhone%20is%20made%20by%20a%20different%20company.%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20example%20of%20this%20was%20by%20Zuckerberg%20himself%2C%20who%20in%202018%20was%20being%20grilled%20over%20Facebook's%20data-collection%20practices.%20Utah%20Sen.%20Orrin%20Hatch%2C%20who%20was%2084%20then%2C%20asked%20how%20Facebook%20could%20be%20free%20to%20users.%20Zuckerberg%20blinked%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSenator%2C%20we%20run%20ads.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fn2H8wx1aBiQ%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Senator%20Asks%20How%20Facebook%20Remains%20Free%2C%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20Smirks%3A%20%E2%80%98We%20Run%20Ads%E2%80%99%20%7C%20NBC%20News%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20things%20were%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram-scandal-crisis-era-mark-zuckerberg-lawsuit-child-predator-report-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETension%20over%20child%20exploitation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20harm%20to%20the%20well-being%20of%20teenagers%20has%20been%20building%20up%20for%20a%20while%2C%20punctuated%20by%20the%20bombshell%20report%20in%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzuckerberg-ignored-execs-calls-to-improve-teen-mental-health-lawsuit-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20had%20willfully%20ignored%20its%20internal%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20effects%20of%20Instagram%20on%20teen%20girls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%2033%20states%20got%20together%20to%20sue%20Meta%20for%20what%20they%20say%20are%20its%20damaging%20effects%20on%20teens.%20Some%20states%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2024%2Fjan%2F25%2Fflorida-social-media-teenager-ban-bill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFlorida%2C%20are%20working%20on%20passing%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20restrict%20teens'%20access%20to%20social%20media%20apps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShocking%20and%20sad%20stories%20about%20sextortion%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0young%20people%20who%20are%20tricked%20into%20producing%20explicit%20images%20and%20then%20are%20extorted%20for%20money%2C%20often%20by%20foreign%20actors%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0have%20been%20in%20the%20news%2C%20and%20parents%20of%20child%20victims%20packed%20the%20audience%20of%20the%20hearing%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EKids%20Online%20Safety%20Act%20has%20bipartisan%20support%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20some%20real%20momentum%20to%20attempt%20to%20pass%20legislation%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20or%20to%20finally%20create%20a%20dedicated%20federal%20regulating%20body%20for%20social%20media.%20And%20unlike%20other%20hearings%20with%20tech%20CEOs%20that%20have%20devolved%20into%20things%20like%20arguing%20about%20political%20bias%20in%20content%20moderation%2C%20this%20is%20a%20largely%20bipartisan%20topic%3A%20Everyone%20wants%20to%20stop%20child%20exploitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20potential%20legislation%20being%20discussed%20is%20not%20exactly%20perfect.%20The%20proposed%20Kids%20Online%20Safety%20Act%2C%20or%20KOSA%2C%20would%20give%20parents%20more%20control%20over%20their%20kids'%20accounts%20and%20would%20require%20platforms%20to%20have%20stricter%20privacy%20settings%20for%20teens.%20This%20sounds%20great%2C%20but%20it%20also%20would%20require%20platforms%20to%20prevent%20teens%20from%20accessing%20content%20deemed%20harmful%20to%20teens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrganizations%20like%20the%20ACLU%20and%20the%20Electronic%20Frontier%20Foundation%20oppose%20KOSA%20because%20they%20say%20it%20could%20go%20too%20far.%20For%20example%2C%20it%20could%20be%20interpreted%20to%20require%20platforms%20to%20stop%20kids%20from%20seeing%20content%20about%20trans%20issues%20or%20even%20discussing%20racism.%20(The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dn2H8wx1aBiQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEFF%20points%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20that%20Sen.%20Marsha%20Blackburn%2C%20Republican%20of%20Tennessee%2C%20one%20of%20the%20bill's%20co-sponsors%2C%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20critical%20race%20theory%20is%20harmful%20to%20kids.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWednesday's%20hearing%20also%20had%20a%20steady%20drumbeat%20of%20wanting%20to%20dismantle%20or%20reform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-section-230-internet-law-communications-decency-act-explained-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%20230%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20rule%20generally%20protects%20internet%20platforms%20from%20being%20liable%20for%20the%20content%20posted%20on%20those%20platforms.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-challenge-section-230-immunity-facebook-google-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%20230%20is%20controversial%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20become%20a%20rallying%20point%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-section-230-facebook-trump-clarence-thomas-ajit-pai-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20some%20conservatives%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20others%2C%20who%20think%20it%20allows%20Big%20Tech%20to%20hide%20from%20criticisms%20that%20it%20isn't%20fair%20to%20all%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20past%20criticism%20of%20the%20law%2C%20though%2C%20Wednesday's%20mentions%20of%20repealing%20it%20mostly%20appealed%20to%20the%20heartstrings%3A%20Getting%20rid%20of%20it%20could%20allow%20grieving%20parents%20to%20sue%20tech%20companies%20for%20compensation%20for%20the%20deaths%20of%20their%20teens%20or%20child%20victims%20of%20exploitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EStill%2C%20the%20safety%20of%20children%20online%20is%20a%20tough%20issue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChild%20exploitation%20and%20harm%20isn't%20an%20easy%20thing%20to%20solve.%20Clearly%2C%20these%20big%20platforms%20haven't%20succeeded%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20motivated%20by%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20internal%20factors%2C%20including%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20there%20were%20some%20magic%20bullet%20to%20stop%20child%20exploitation%2C%20I%20truly%20believe%20the%20companies%20would've%20used%20it%20by%20now.%20Whether%20lawmakers'%20plans%20to%20regulate%20and%20fix%20this%20will%20work%20is%20anyone's%20guess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20now%20enough%20wind%20behind%20this%20issue%20to%20make%20%3Cem%3Esomething%3C%2Fem%3E%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-mark-zuckerberg-senate-hearing-child-exploitation-social-media-law-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706746622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65badd9d43bb77284ba2578e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-mark-zuckerberg-senate-hearing-child-exploitation-social-media-law-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20apology%20to%20parents%20might%20have%20been%20theatrics%2C%20but%20this%20time%2C%20there's%20enough%20rage%20that%20some